4 §1374. Penalty
5 * * *
6 C. In addition to the authority provided in Subsection B of this Section, the
7 board may assess administrative fines of not less than five hundred dollars and not
8 more than five thousand dollars against any person, or employing entity, per
9 violation of any provision of this Chapter or any rule adopted by the board pursuant
10 to its authority as provided by this Chapter. An administrative fine assessed pursuant
11 to this Subsection shall not be imposed unless notice and an opportunity to be heard
12 has occurred, in accordance with the Administrative Procedure Act. Any
13 administrative fine imposed pursuant to this Subsection shall not require the filing
14 of a consumer complaint and shall be independent of any criminal prosecution
15 resulting from the violation giving rise to the imposition of the administrative fine.
16 D. Nothing in this Section shall be construed to supersede the exceptions
17 provided for in R.S. 37:1376 and 1377.
