19 §1377. Definitions; exceptions
20 * * *
21 B.(1) Journeyman plumber. A "journeyman plumber" is a natural person who
22 possesses the necessary qualifications and knowledge to install, alter, repair, and
23 maintain plumbing systems; is licensed as such by the board; is supervised by a
24 master plumber; and is in the employ of an employing entity.
25 (2) Residential plumber limited. A " residential plumber limited" is a natural
26 person who possesses the necessary qualifications and knowledge to install, alter,
27 repair, and maintain plumbing systems and is licensed by the board to install, alter,
28 repair, and maintain plumbing systems in one- and two-family dwellings at the
29 direction of a master plumber without the supervision of a journeyman plumber.
30 C.(1) Apprentice plumber. An "apprentice plumber" is a natural person
31 engaged in learning the plumbing trade by working under the direct, on-the-job
32 supervision of a journeyman plumber and in the employ of an employing entity.
33 Apprentice plumbers shall be indentured in an apprenticeship program approved by
34 Louisiana Works or, unindentured and in the employ of an employing entity, or
35 unindentured and in the employ of an employing entity while enrolled in an
36 approved training program through the Louisiana Community and Technical College
37 System.
38 (2) Apprentice gas fitter. An "apprentice gas fitter" is a natural person
39 engaged in learning the gas fitting trade by working under the direct, on-the-job
40 supervision of a gas fitter and in the employ of an employing entity. Apprentice gas
41 fitters shall be indentured in an apprenticeship program approved by Louisiana
42 Works or may be, unindentured and in the employ of an employing entity, or
43 unindentured and in the employ of an employing entity while enrolled in an
44 approved training program through the Louisiana Community and Technical College
45 System.
