47 §1381. Reporting requirements
48 A. The legislature hereby recognizes the importance of the occupational field
49 of plumbing and the necessity of expanding recruitment, especially in the population
50 of minority students, as the pool of licensed plumbing professionals has not grown
51 at the same pace of need for the occupation. It is the intent of the legislature that the
52 board increase outreach to minority students for recruitment into the occupational
53 field of plumbing.
54 B. The board, in consultation and collaboration with the Board of Elementary
55 and Secondary Education, the Louisiana Community and Technology College
56 System, and any other vocational programs identified by the board, shall survey all
57 efforts in effect to encourage minority participation in the occupational field of
58 plumbing. No later than April 12, 2027, the board shall submit a report of the survey
59 to the House Committee on Commerce and the Senate Committee on Commerce,
60 Consumer Protection and International Affairs. The report shall include but not be
61 limited to the following:
62 (1) The total number of licensed plumbers as of August 1, 2026.
